## Description {#details}

Non-owning <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/symbolstringpool">SymbolStringPool</a> entry pointer.

Instances are comparable with <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/symbolstringptr">SymbolStringPtr</a> instances and guaranteed to have the same hash, but do not affect the ref-count of the pooled string (and are therefore cheaper to copy).

NonOwningSymbolStringPtrs are silently invalidated if the pool entry&#39;s ref-count drops to zero, so they should only be used in contexts where a corresponding <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/symbolstringptr">SymbolStringPtr</a> is known to exist (which will guarantee that the ref-count stays above zero). E.g. in a graph where nodes are represented by SymbolStringPtrs the edges can be represented by pairs of NonOwningSymbolStringPtrs and this will make the introduction of deletion of edges cheaper.
